'''Nasu Onsen Shrine''' (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nasu District|ja|那須郡|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nasu Town|ja|那須町|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == It is said to have been founded during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|用明天皇|qq=draft}} (reigned: {{ill|629|ja|629|qq=draft}} – {{ill|641|ja|641|qq=draft}}).<ref name="jre">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://sightseeing.jrnets.co.jp/detail/spot/4418.html|title=Nasu Onsen Shrine (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】)|publisher={{ill|East Japan Railway Company|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft}}|work=観光スポット・イベント情報|accessdate=2022-03-04}}</ref> In ancient times, in the 11th year of the {{ill|Jōgan era|ja|上元|qq=draft}} ({{ill|869|ja|869|qq=draft}}), the shrine was awarded the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従四位上|qq=draft}} and its name appears in the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft}}’s {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Jinmyōchō|lt_ja=神名帳|qq=draft}}. In the late {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft}}, during the {{ill|Battle of Yashima|ja|屋島の戦い|qq=draft}}, when {{ill|Nasu Yoichi|ja|那須与一|qq=draft}} took aim at the fan’s target, he prayed to Nasu Onsen Shrine, exclaiming, “Namu {{ill|Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|ja|八幡大菩薩|qq=draft}}, and beyond that, the divine spirit of our country, {{ill|Nikkō Two Arashiyama Shrine|ja|日光二荒山神社|lt=Gongen of Nikkō|lt_ja=日光権現|qq=draft}}{{ill|Utsunomiya Two Arashiyama Shrine|ja|宇都宮二荒山神社|1=Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine|lt=Utsunomiya|lt_ja=宇都宮|qq=draft}}, Nasu Onsen Daimyōjin, may you let my arrow strike dead center of that fan.” His successful shot brought him great renown, and he became the head of {{ill|Nasu District|ja|那須郡|qq=draft}}; after his triumphant return, in gratitude for the divine favor, he donated a grand shrine building and offered items such as the kabura arrow, the toad-eye arrow, the征矢, a cypress fan, and a torii. The local people collectively enshrined the Onsen Shrine, and on June 19 of the 3rd year of the {{ill|Jōkyō era|ja|貞享|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1686|ja|1686|qq=draft}}), it was conferred the Rank of {{ill|Shoichii|ja|正一位|qq=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://nasu-yuzen.jp/sp/|title=宗教法人 那須温泉神社|publisher=Nasu Onsen Shrine|accessdate=2022-02-23}}</ref> Following Yoichi’s example, many continue to visit for prayers for certain victory.<ref name="jre"/>
Within the shrine grounds are the three torii contributed by Yoichi, as well as the {{ill|Water Koto Cave|ja|水琴窟|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Sazare Stone|ja|さざれ石|qq=draft}}.<ref name="jre"/>
Behind the shrine, there is a {{ill|Sesshōseki|ja|殺生石|qq=draft}} which is said to be the petrified form of {{ill|Tamamo-no-Mae|ja|玉藻前|qq=draft}}.{{citation needed|なすゆせんしんしや}}
== Sub-shrines == : '''Atago Shrine''' 祭神 - {{ill|Kagutsuchi|ja|カグツチ|lt=Hikatsuri no Mikoto|lt_ja=火産霊命|qq=draft}} : '''Mitate Shrine''' 祭神 - {{ill|Amanoyowahime|ja|天児屋命|1=Ame-no-Koyane|lt=Amanoyowane no Mikoto|lt_ja=天児屋根命|qq=draft}}, Kano Saburō Yukihiro : '''Sorei Shrine''' : '''Kotohira Shrine''' : '''Smallpox Shrine''' : '''Shinmei Shrine''' : '''Mountain Shrine''' : '''Wakaji Shrine''' : '''Tenma Tenjin''' 祭神 - {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|lt=Lord Sugawara|lt_ja=公|qq=draft}} : '''Nine-tailed Inari Shrine''' 祭神 - {{ill|Nine-tailed Fox|ja|九尾の狐|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Tamamo-no-Mae|ja|玉藻前|qq=draft}})
<gallery widths="200"> File:Nasuyuzen3.jpg|Mitate Shrine (見立神社) File:Nasuyuzen4.jpg|Sorei Shrine (祖霊社) File:Nasuyuzen2.jpg|Nine-tailed Inari Shrine (九尾稲荷神社) </gallery>
