== Overview == It is said to have been founded during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|用明天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Jomei|qq=}} (reigned: {{ill|629|ja|629|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/629|qq=}} – {{ill|641|ja|641|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/641|qq=}}).<ref name="jre">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://sightseeing.jrnets.co.jp/detail/spot/4418.html|title=Nasu Onsen Shrine (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】)|publisher={{ill|East Japan Railway Company|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/East Japan Railway Company|qq=}}|work=観光スポット・イベント情報|accessdate=2022-03-04}}</ref> In ancient times, in the 11th year of the {{ill|Jōgan era|ja|上元|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan era|qq=}} ({{ill|869|ja|869|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/869|qq=}}), the shrine was awarded the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従四位上|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=}} and its name appears in the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki|qq=}}’s {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Jinmyōchō|lt_ja=神名帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}. In the late {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}}, during the {{ill|Battle of Yashima|ja|屋島の戦い|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Yashima|qq=}}, when {{ill|Nasu Yoichi|ja|那須与一|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nasu Yoichi|qq=}} took aim at the fan’s target, he prayed to Nasu Onsen Shrine, exclaiming, “Namu {{ill|Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|ja|八幡大菩薩|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|qq=}}, and beyond that, the divine spirit of our country, {{ill|Nikkō Two Arashiyama Shrine|ja|日光二荒山神社|lt=Gongen of Nikkō|lt_ja=日光権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nikkō Two Arashiyama Shrine|qq=}}{{ill|Utsunomiya Two Arashiyama Shrine|ja|宇都宮二荒山神社|1=Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine|lt=Utsunomiya|lt_ja=宇都宮|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Two Arashiyama Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine|qq=}}, Nasu Onsen Daimyōjin, may you let my arrow strike dead center of that fan.” His successful shot brought him great renown, and he became the head of {{ill|Nasu District|ja|那須郡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nasu District|qq=}}; after his triumphant return, in gratitude for the divine favor, he donated a grand shrine building and offered items such as the kabura arrow, the toad-eye arrow, the征矢, a cypress fan, and a torii. The local people collectively enshrined the Onsen Shrine, and on June 19 of the 3rd year of the {{ill|Jōkyō era|ja|貞享|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōkyō era|qq=}} ({{ill|1686|ja|1686|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1686|qq=}}), it was conferred the Rank of {{ill|Shoichii|ja|正一位|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shoichii|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://nasu-yuzen.jp/sp/|title=宗教法人 那須温泉神社|publisher=Nasu Onsen Shrine|accessdate=2022-02-23}}</ref> Following Yoichi’s example, many continue to visit for prayers for certain victory.<ref name="jre"/>
Within the shrine grounds are the three torii contributed by Yoichi, as well as the {{ill|Water Koto Cave|ja|水琴窟|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Water Koto Cave|qq=}} and the {{ill|Sazare Stone|ja|さざれ石|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sazare Stone|qq=}}.<ref name="jre"/>
Behind the shrine, there is a {{ill|Sesshōseki|ja|殺生石|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sesshōseki|qq=}} which is said to be the petrified form of {{ill|Tamamo-no-Mae|ja|玉藻前|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamamo-no-Mae|qq=}}.
