== Overview == It is said to have been founded during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Jomei]] (reigned: {{ill|629|ja|629|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/629|qq=}} – {{ill|641|ja|641|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/641|qq=}}).<ref name="jre">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://sightseeing.jrnets.co.jp/detail/spot/4418.html|title=Nasu Onsen Shrine (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】)|publisher=[[:en:East Japan Railway Company|East Japan Railway Company]]|work=観光スポット・イベント情報|accessdate=2022-03-04}}</ref> In ancient times, in the 11th year of the {{ill|Jōgan era|ja|上元|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan era|qq=}} ({{ill|869|ja|869|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/869|qq=}}), the shrine was awarded the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従四位上|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=}} and its name appears in the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]’s {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Jinmyōchō|lt_ja=神名帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}. In the late [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], during the [[:en:Battle of Yashima|Battle of Yashima]], when [[:en:Nasu no Yoichi|Nasu Yoichi]] took aim at the fan’s target, he prayed to Nasu Onsen Shrine, exclaiming, “Namu {{ill|Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|ja|八幡大菩薩|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|qq=}}, and beyond that, the divine spirit of our country, [[:en:Futarasan shrine|Gongen of Nikkō]][[:en:Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine|Utsunomiya]], Nasu Onsen Daimyōjin, may you let my arrow strike dead center of that fan.” His successful shot brought him great