'''Nasu Onsen Shrine''' (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shrine]] located in [[:en:Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi Prefecture]], [[:en:Nasu District, Tochigi|Nasu District]], [[:en:Nasu, Tochigi|Nasu Town]].
== Overview == It is said to have been founded during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Jomei]] (reigned: {{ill|629|ja|629|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/629|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}} – {{ill|641|ja|641|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/641|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}}).<ref name="jre">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://sightseeing.jrnets.co.jp/detail/spot/4418.html|title=Nasu Onsen Shrine (那須温泉神社【なすゆぜんじんじゃ】)|publisher=[[:en:East Japan Railway Company|East Japan Railway Company]]|work=観光スポット・イベント情報|accessdate=2022-03-04}}</ref> In ancient times, in the 11th year of the {{ill|Jōgan era|ja|上元|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan era|qq=}} ({{ill|869|ja|869|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/869|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 800}}), the shrine was awarded the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従四位上|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 従四位}} and its name appears in the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]’s {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Jinmyōchō|lt_ja=神名帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}. In the late [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], during the [[:en:Battle of Yashima|Battle of Yashima]], when [[:en:Nasu no Yoichi|Nasu Yoichi]] took aim at the fan’s target, he prayed to Nasu Onsen Shrine, exclaiming, “Namu {{ill|Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|ja|八幡大菩薩|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Great Bodhisattva|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 八幡神}}, and beyond that, the divine spirit of our country, [[:en:Futarasan shrine|Gongen of Nikkō]][[:en:Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine|Utsunomiya]], Nasu Onsen Daimyōjin, may you let my arrow strike dead center of that fan.” His successful shot brought him great renown, and he became the head of [[:en:Nasu District, Tochigi|Nasu District]]; after his triumphant return, in gratitude for the divine favor, he donated a grand shrine building and offered items such as the kabura arrow, the toad-eye arrow, the征矢, a cypress fan, and a torii. The local people collectively enshrined the Onsen Shrine, and on June 19 of the 3rd year of the [[:en:Jōkyō|Jōkyō era]] ({{ill|1686|ja|1686|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1686|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), it was conferred the Rank of {{ill|Shoichii|ja|正一位|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shoichii|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://nasu-yuzen.jp/sp/|title=宗教法人 那須温泉神社|publisher=Nasu Onsen Shrine|accessdate=2022-02-23}}</ref> Following Yoichi’s example, many continue to visit for prayers for certain victory.<ref name="jre"/>
Within the shrine grounds are the three torii contributed by Yoichi, as well as the [[:en:Suikinkutsu|Water Koto Cave]] and the {{ill|Sazare Stone|ja|さざれ石|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sazare Stone|qq=}}.<ref name="jre"/>
Behind the shrine, there is a [[:en:Sessho-seki|Sesshōseki]] which is said to be the petrified form of [[:en:Tamamo-no-Mae|Tamamo-no-Mae]].
== Sub-shrines == : '''Atago Shrine''' 祭神 - [[:en:Kagu-tsuchi|Hikatsuri no Mikoto]] : '''Mitate Shrine''' 祭神 - [[:en:Ame-no-Koyane|Amanoyowane no Mikoto]], Kano Saburō Yukihiro : '''Sorei Shrine''' : '''Kotohira Shrine''' : '''Smallpox Shrine''' : '''Shinmei Shrine''' : '''Mountain Shrine''' : '''Wakaji Shrine''' : '''Tenma Tenjin''' 祭神 - {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|lt=Lord Sugawara|lt_ja=公|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} : '''Nine-tailed Inari Shrine''' 祭神 - [[:en:Nine-tailed fox|Nine-tailed Fox]] ([[:en:Tamamo-no-Mae|Tamamo-no-Mae]])
